Whether we are aware of it or not, when we are communicating with others our bodies are giving off signals. Our non-verbal language sometimes speaks louder than the words we say. What it looks like:
Facial expressions
Has anyone asked you, ‚Äúwhat‚Äôs with the face?‚Äù, when you were actually thinking about something unrelated to the conversation?
Body Language 
Are you walking with her head held high or chin down, what does that say about your confidence?
Gestures 
How animated do you get with your hands when you are excited or angry?
Eye contact
Remember ‚Äúthat look‚Äù your partner gave you just the other day, was it out of anger of affection?
Touch
A  bear hug, harsh grab of the arm, a kick in the shins, or a kiss all express how we are feeling
Personal space 
Social distancing is real, when is the last time you had to take a step back because someone was just too close?
Voice
Last but not least, watch your tone because it‚Äôs often not what you say but how you say it. 

Today just be conscious of your nonverbals, you may be surprised what you uncover

